name: Baby Boomers
description:
Baby boomers are the generation after the silent generation and generation X. The generation is generally defined as people born from 1946 to 1964, during the post–World War II baby boom. Baby Boomers tend to be more disciplined, obedient, organized, and reliable than the younger generation. Their second highest personal value is "safety in society and the nation", which includes social stability, national security, and social order. For them, life is about a strong country and a stable society.
